"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":4,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%   42.782      1 -total\",\"100.00%   42.782      1 Template:Version030\",\" 97.15%   41.561      1 Template:Version\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240916092339\",\"ttl\":86400,\"transientcontent\":false}}});});</script><script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":152});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{version030}}\n\n'''Riposte''' is an [[ego]] exclusive to the [[unrandart]] [[fencer's gloves]]. If a player [[Dodging|dodges]] or [[shield|blocks]] a monster's melee attack while wearing these gloves, there is a 1/3 chance they will riposte, letting them perform a reflexive attack against the monster (like a [[minotaur]] headbutt). A monster can only be riposted once per their turn. If you riposte, the effects from an [[amulet of the acrobat]] are negated.\n\nRiposte probability does not take into account weapon skill or weapon delay. They also do not interact with certain enemy passive abilities, such as [[hydra]] decapitation or [[spiny]] retaliation.\n\n== History ==\n*Prior to [[0.29]], riposte did not work on [[shield|blocked]] attacks.\n*Prior to [[0.28]], riposte was an innate quality of all [[Long Blades]] (which had reduced base damage to compensate).\n*Riposte was introduced in [[0.19]]."}